The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 January is 185,881 (21,423.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 January, there were 9,271 new confirmed cases (1,068.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 January, there were 7,099 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 31% (2,172 extra cases).
